      "source": [
        "We need to normalize the data before training. For the air pollution columns we save the normalization parameters. Later with them we can convert the forecasted outputs to pollution concentrations."
      ]
    },
    {
      "metadata": {
        "id": "Zcs2bTwt3fV8",
        "colab_type": "code",
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/",
          "height": 235
        },
        "outputId": "386e6cac-0cd2-41d4-8d0d-f021e6fce497"
      },
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# variables for later renormalization\n",
        "label_mean = df['Teleki'].mean()\n",
        "label_std = df['Teleki'].std()\n",
        "print(f\"pollution columns mean: {label_mean}\")\n",
        "print(f\"pollution columns std: {label_std}\")\n",
        "#%%\n",
        "# normalize columns with (c-mean)/std\n",
        "df[['temp_avr','temp_max','temp_min','pres','u','v','prec','Teleki']] \\\n",
        "= df[['temp_avr','temp_max','temp_min','pres','u','v','prec','Teleki']] \\\n",
        ".apply(lambda x: (x - x.mean()) / x.std())\n",
        "\n",
        "df.head()"
      ],

    {
      "metadata": {
        "id": "eA9NFTK69osr",
        "colab_type": "text"
      },
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "We convert the day of week and year of week to coordinates on a one radius circel. This way the days closer to each other will have similar coordinates. We hope that this helps the model to understand some periodic behavior of the dataset."
      ]
    },
    {
      "metadata": {
        "id": "Iob1Ph2W32jZ",
        "colab_type": "code",
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/",
          "height": 564
        },
        "outputId": "c98944df-cbb7-430c-feae-d428774f2456"
      },
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# Convert day of year and day of week numbers to coordinates of a point\n",
        "# on a circle. This way day of year and day of week will become periodic \n",
        "# data\n",
        "# first convert days to scale\n",
        "df['day_week'] = df['datetime'].dt.dayofweek*(360/7)\n",
        "df['day_year'] = df['datetime'].dt.dayofyear*(360/365)\n",
        "# then convert scales to coordinates on 1 radius circle\n",
        "# rad = 4.0*atan(1.0)/180\n",
        "df['dw_x'] = -np.sin((4.0*np.arctan(1.0)/180)*df['day_week'])\n",
        "df['dw_y'] = -np.cos((4.0*np.arctan(1.0)/180)*df['day_week'])\n",
        "df['dy_x'] = -np.sin((4.0*np.arctan(1.0)/180)*df['day_year'])\n",
        "df['dy_y'] = -np.cos((4.0*np.arctan(1.0)/180)*df['day_year'])\n",
        "\n",
        "df.plot.scatter(x='dy_x', y='dy_y')\n",
        "df.plot.scatter(x='dw_x', y='dw_y')"
      ],
      "execution_count": 5,
      "outputs": [

      "source": [
        "In real situation for a given day we know the weather (from a weather forecast, which here is represented by the weather station data) and the airpollution a day before (Teleki_ystd). So we add to a row of parameters the airpollution of the prior day. The air pollution of the given day (Teleki) will be our label. We want our forecast as close to this label as possible."
      ]
    },
    {
      "metadata": {
        "id": "nOXlp_Nm3j7W",
        "colab_type": "code",
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/",
          "height": 198
        },
        "outputId": "989291ba-ed9c-4387-b846-ed613f7483ee"
      },
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# make the yesterday day column\n",
        "df['Teleki_ystd'] = df['Teleki'].shift(+1)\n",
        "# fill the missing day value with next day\n",
        "df['Teleki_ystd'] = df['Teleki_ystd'].fillna(method='bfill')\n",
        "# reorder columns, last column will be the label data\n",
        "df = df[['datetime','dy_x','dy_y','dw_x','dw_y',\n",
        "         'temp_avr','temp_max','temp_min','pres', \n",
        "         'u','v','prec','Teleki_ystd','Teleki']]\n",
        "df.head()"
      ],

      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "Split the database to train, validation and test data."
      ]
    },
    {
      "metadata": {
        "id": "a4Ha2QJAr7XO",
        "colab_type": "code",
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/",
          "height": 72
        },
        "outputId": "7fc3b917-3639-4742-fd88-a9e0d70f9492"
      },
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# build the pytorch train, validation and test sets\n",
        "# train data\n",
        "mask = (df['datetime'] < '2017-01-01')\n",
        "df_train = df.loc[mask].drop(columns=['datetime'])\n",
        "# train tensors\n",
        "train_data = torch.tensor(df_train.values).float()\n",
        "print(train_data.shape)\n",
        "\n",
        "# validation data\n",
        "mask = (df['datetime'] < '2018-01-01') & (df['datetime'] >= '2017-01-01')\n",
        "df_valid = df.loc[mask].drop(columns=['datetime'])\n",
        "# validation tensors\n",
        "valid_data = torch.tensor(df_valid.values).float()\n",
        "print(valid_data.shape)\n",
        "\n",
        "# test data\n",
        "mask = (df['datetime'] >= '2018-01-01')\n",
        "df_test = df.loc[mask].drop(columns=['datetime'])\n",
        "# validation tensors\n",
        "test_data = torch.tensor(df_test.values).float()\n",
        "print(test_data.shape)"
      ],
      "execution_count": 7,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "stream",
          "text": [
            "torch.Size([2192, 13])\n",
            "torch.Size([365, 13])\n",
            "torch.Size([361, 13])\n"
          ],
          "name": "stdout"
        }

        "# define and print the net\n",
        "number_of_features = train_data.shape[1] - 1 # -1 because last column is label\n",
        "n_hidden=256\n",
        "n_layers=3\n",
        "net = pmod.instantiate_model(number_of_features, 1, n_hidden, n_layers, train_on_gpu)\n",
        "print(net)"
      ],
      "execution_count": 9,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "stream",
          "text": [
            "LSTMForecaster(\n",
            "  (lstm): LSTM(12, 256, num_layers=3, batch_first=True, dropout=0.5)\n",
            "  (dropout): Dropout(p=0.5)\n",
            "  (fc): Linear(in_features=256, out_features=1, bias=True)\n",
            ")\n"

      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "We train our model. During training the step with the smallest validation loss will be saved. Later we will load back the modell with the smallest loss."
      ]
    },
    {
      "metadata": {
        "id": "Z2z0_ptTvwU8",

      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# train the model\n",
        "cp_name='cp_withtimeperiod.pth'\n",
        "batch_size = 5\n",
        "seq_length = 30\n",
        "n_epochs = 100 # start smaller if you are just testing initial behavior\n",
        "pmod.train( net, train_data, valid_data, epochs=n_epochs, \n",
        "            batch_size=batch_size, seq_length=seq_length, lr=0.001, \n",
        "            checkpoint_name=cp_name, train_on_gpu=train_on_gpu)"
      ],

      "source": [
        "# load back best model\n",
        "with open(cp_name, 'rb') as f:\n",
        "    checkpoint = torch.load(f)\n",
        "  \n",
        "net_best = pmod.instantiate_model(checkpoint['input_size'], checkpoint['output_size'], n_hidden=checkpoint['n_hidden'], n_layers=checkpoint['n_layers'], train_on_gpu=train_on_gpu)\n",
        "net_best.load_state_dict(checkpoint['state_dict'])\n",
        "if(train_on_gpu):\n",
        "  net_best.cuda()"
      ],
      "execution_count": 0,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "metadata": {
        "id": "lo7wiccdBU48",
        "colab_type": "text"
      },
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "Use the model with test_data to forecast the first day pollution (day0) and the second day pollution (day1). For the forecast of the second day pollution we use our own forecast of first day pollution."
      ]
    },
    {
      "metadata": {
        "id": "N49_0N1U4uw7",
        "colab_type": "code",
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/",
          "height": 54
        },
        "outputId": "95d8b40d-1c74-489c-c40f-43779964ba6e"
      },
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# check test data\n",
        "# model to evaluation mode\n",
        "net_best.eval()\n",
        "test_losses_MSE = [[], []]\n",
        "target_list = [[], []]\n",
        "forecast_list = [[], []]\n",
        "# during test we simulate the implementation of the deployed usage:\n",
        "batch_size = 1\n",
        "seq_length = 1\n",
        "\n",
        "criterionMSE = nn.MSELoss()\n",
        "\n",
        "counter = 0\n",
        "# we will examine the model forecast for the next day where the\n",
        "# pollution is unknown and for the they after that\n",
        "# we implement two data-getter for that, one for the first forecast day\n",
        "# and an other for the next forecast day\n",
        "batches_day0 = pmod.get_batches(test_data, batch_size, seq_length)\n",
        "batches_day1 = pmod.get_batches(test_data, batch_size, seq_length)\n",
        "next(batches_day1)\n",
        "\n",
        "# data for first forecast day\n",
        "for inputs_day0, targets_day0 in batches_day0:\n",
        "    counter+=1\n",
        "    # break before batches_day1 runs out\n",
        "    if counter >= len(test_data):\n",
        "        break\n",
        "    # data for second forecast day    \n",
        "    inputs_day1, targets_day1 = next(batches_day1)\n",
        "    if(train_on_gpu):\n",
        "      inputs_day0, targets_day0 = inputs_day0.cuda(), targets_day0.cuda()\n",
        "      inputs_day1, targets_day1 = inputs_day1.cuda(), targets_day1.cuda()\n",
        "\n",
        "    # calculate forecast for day0\n",
        "    test_h = net.init_hidden(batch_size)\n",
        "    output_day0, test_h = net_best(inputs_day0, test_h)\n",
        "    test_loss_MSE_day0 = criterionMSE(output_day0, targets_day0.view(batch_size*seq_length,-1))\n",
        "    test_losses_MSE[0].append(test_loss_MSE_day0.item())\n",
        "    target_list[0].append(targets_day0.item())\n",
        "    forecast_list[0].append(output_day0.item())\n",
        "\n",
        "    # need to clone tensor, without this the modification of tensor would affect other data as well\n",
        "    inputs_day1.data = inputs_day1.clone()\n",
        "    # we don't change the weather parameters for inputs_day1, because that is our weather forecast,\n",
        "    # but we change the last number, because that is our pollution forecast from day0\n",
        "    # our beforday pollution in day1 is the pollution forecast of day0\n",
        "    inputs_day1[0][0][-1] = output_day0.item()\n",
        "    # calculate forecast for the day1\n",
        "    test_h = net.init_hidden(batch_size)\n",
        "    output_day1, test_h = net_best(inputs_day1, test_h)\n",
        "    test_loss_MSE_day1 = criterionMSE(output_day1, targets_day1.view(batch_size*seq_length,-1))\n",
        "    test_losses_MSE[1].append(test_loss_MSE_day1.item())\n",
        "    target_list[1].append(targets_day1.item())\n",
        "    forecast_list[1].append(output_day1.item())\n",
        "\n",
        "print( \"test losses MSE for day0: {:.4f}\".format(np.mean(test_losses_MSE[0])))\n",
        "print( \"test losses MSE for day1: {:.4f}\".format(np.mean(test_losses_MSE[1])))"
      ],
      "execution_count": 12,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "stream",
          "text": [
            "test losses MSE for day0: 0.3315\n",
            "test losses MSE for day1: 0.4738\n"
          ],
          "name": "stdout"
        }
      ]

      "metadata": {
        "id": "AfjxMg5YBi6b",
        "colab_type": "text"

      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "To examine the forecast performance we convert back our data to the original form. This way we get back the μg/m3 concentration numbers. "
      ]
    },
    {
      "metadata": {
        "id": "Z1fufj5U42bJ",
        "colab_type": "code",
        "colab": {}
      },
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# renormalize data to get back the pm10 concentrations\n",
        "forecast_concentration_day0 = [i * label_std + label_mean for i in forecast_list[0]]\n",
        "target_concentration_day0 = [i * label_std + label_mean for i in target_list[0]]\n",
        "abs_error_day0 = [np.abs(a - b) for a, b in zip(forecast_concentration_day0, target_concentration_day0)]\n",
        "\n",
        "forecast_concentration_day1 = [i * label_std + label_mean for i in forecast_list[1]]\n",
        "target_concentration_day1 = [i * label_std + label_mean for i in target_list[1]]\n",
        "abs_error_day1 = [np.abs(a - b) for a, b in zip(forecast_concentration_day1, target_concentration_day1)]"
      ],
      "execution_count": 0,
      "outputs": []
    },

      "metadata": {
        "id": "8rdiwLRdUgQ5",

      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "The most simple forecast is if we say that something tomorrow will be the same as something today. We hope that our model is better than that. First calculat the errors for this 'noforecast' forecast, only for day0."
      ]
    },
    {
      "metadata": {
        "id": "WQsjZ7VbU406",
        "colab_type": "code",

        "outputId": "a3c02211-e67e-4bea-9670-2af284679b9d"
      },
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "abs_error_day0_noforecast = [np.abs(a - b) for a, b in zip(target_concentration_day1, target_concentration_day0)]\n",
        "print(\"ERRORS OF NO FORECAST - we except the same as yesterday\")\n",
        "print(f\"Mean Abs Error no forecast: {np.mean(abs_error_day0_noforecast)} μg/m3\")\n",
